Day 3 - Chapter 1
1) Conditional Statements:- 
=> Conditional statements let your program make decisions: “if this is true, do this; otherwise, do something else.”

Basic if statement:- 
age = 18
if age >= 18:
    print("You are an adult.")

Basic if - else statement:-
age = 16
if age >= 18:
    print("You are an adult.")
else:
    print("You are a minor.")

Basic if – elif – else:- 
score = 85
if score >= 90:
    print("Grade A")
elif score >= 75:
    print("Grade B")
elif score >= 60:
    print("Grade C")
else:
    print("Grade D")
